gps4earth - your gps position for google earth

1) Introduction
2) Requirements
3) Installation
4) Usage
5) Contact

---------------------------------------------------------------------
Introduction

gps4earth is used to display your current gps position in google earth as a
red marker. Your curent gps position is fetched through gpsd.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
Requirements

* python 2.5, 2.6
* google earth
* apache httpd with cgi support

---------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation

To install gps4earth into your apache installation type the following as root:

$ make install

---------------------------------------------------------------------
Usage

After installation gps4earth can be used. Start your apache server and google
earth. Open the file etc/GPS.kmz in google earth. This will display a red
marker with your current GPS position in the map.

